comments: Harden (BKN) makes contact to Randle's (NYK) arm and affects his shot attempt.
During the drive, Burks (NYK) runs alongside Harden (BKN) and any side to side contact as they come together is marginal.
Randle (NYK) legally contests Durant's (BKN) jump shot attempt.  Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
All Technical Fouls are reviewed by League Operations.
Harden (BKN) maintains a legal guarding position on Randle (NYK) during the drive.
Durant (BKN) briefly grasps Robinson's (NYK) arm and marginal contact occurs, which does not affect Robinson's ability to secure the rebound.

Harden (BKN) reaches in and makes clean ball contact to dislodge it from Randle (NYK) at the end of his drive. Any follow-through contact with Randle's arm or Durant's (BKN) body after the dislodge is deemed incidental.
Harden (BKN) ends his dribble and lands on two feet prior to making the pass.
Robinson (NYK) is in the paint for less than three seconds when the shot is imminent.
During the rebound, Aldridge (BKN) initiates the engagement with Rose (NYK) and marginal contact occurs as they disengage to pursue the loose ball.
Harden (BKN) avoids contact with Randle (NYK) during his dunk at the basket.
Randle (NYK) makes marginal contact to Durant's (BKN) side as he gathers the ball on his driving shot attempt.
Robinson (NYK) places a resting forearm on Aldridge's (BKN) back and marginal contact occurs as he pursues the rebound.
Robinson (NYK) is the last player to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds.
Harden (BKN) releases his inbounds pass within 5 seconds.
During the inbound, Aldridge (BKN) establishes himself in a screening position in Randle's (NYK) path and absorbs the contact on the screen.
Aldridge (BKN) makes marginal foot to foot contact with Quickley (NYK) as he establishes his screening position.
Randle (NYK) extends his arm out and makes contact with Durant's (BKN) arm on his way to the ball, which affects Durant's dunk attempt.
Durant (BKN) engages with Robinson (NYK) on the pick, and marginal contact occurs as he slides his hand off of Robinson's front during his roll to the basket.
Quickley (NYK) moves alongside Aldridge's (BKN) path and marginal contact occurs as they engage and disengage on the perimeter.
Bembry (BKN) moves laterally into Burks' (NYK) path and makes contact with his lower body, which affects his SQBR.
Harden (BKN) has his hands on Rose's (NYK) side and marginal contact occurs, which does not restrict his FOM and ability to set both of his intended screens during the inbounds.
Rose (NYK) establishes himself in a screening position in Brown's (BKN) path and absorbs the contact on the screen.
During the inbounds, Quickley (NYK) establishes himself in a screening position in Johnson's (BKN) path and absorbs the contact on the screen.
Fournier (NYK) does not extend his arms out and deliver contact to Brown (BKN) as they approach the off-ball screen.
Brown (BKN) legally contests Fournier's (NYK) jump shot attempt.
Rose (NYK) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he is imminently exiting.
Aldridge (BKN) has a resting hand on Robinson's (NYK) back and marginal contact occurs, which does not dislodge Robinson.
Aldridge (BKN) is in the lane for longer than three seconds.
Robinson (NYK) extends his arm out and makes contact with Johnson's (BKN) wrist, which affects his shot near the rim.
Harden (BKN) legally contests Fournier's (NYK) last second shot attempt.
